{"title":"AASQ #119: Why full group sets for Gravel? Rotor, FSA and MicroSHIFT discuss","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/05/21/aasq-119-why-full-group-sets-for-gravel-rotor-fsa-and-microshift-discuss/","date":1621608526000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><em>We know, there’s no such thing as a stupid question. But there are some questions you might not want to ask your local shop or riding buddies. AASQ is our weekly series where we get to the bottom of your questions – serious or otherwise. Hit the link at the bottom of the post to submit your own question.</em></p><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>Welcome back to the Bikerumor&nbsp;<em>Ask A Stupid Question</em> series. This week, the good guys from MicroSHIFT, Rotor and FSA are joining us to discuss why they do, or don’t offer complete group sets dedicated to gravel riding. Contributing today are:</p><ul><li>Lori Barrett, the Managing Director of <a href=\"https://rotorbike.com/catalog/default/rotor/road.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Rotor Bike</a></li><li>John McKone, Road Marketing at <a href=\"https://www.fullspeedahead.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Full Speed Ahead</a></li><li>Gus Juffer, Brand Manager at <a href=\"https://www.microshift.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MicroSHIFT</a></li></ul><p><strong>Why full group sets for gravel? The market is clamoring for the absolute widest gearing possible and that would come via compatibility with mountain bike gearing. This could have been accomplished with the introduction of 10, 11 and 12 speed shifters and a couple of cranksets.</strong></p><p><strong>Rotor: </strong>For ROTOR, we asked ourselves the same question: why a specific groupset for gravel? That’s why we introduced the 1×13 as a modular 1x group, which means its single wide-range derailleur is capable for Road, Gravel, MTB or TT.</p><figure id=\"attachment_259494\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-259494\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette.jpg\" alt=\"revel mtb with rotor 1x13 drivetrain 13 speed wide range cassette\" width=\"1200\" height=\"801\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-1068x713.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-629x420.jpg 629w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-1068x713.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081424/Revel-1x13-rotor-drivetrain-13-speed-cassette-629x420.jpg 629w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-259494\">The <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/09/04/rotor-1x13-hydraulic-mountain-bike-group-is-here-plus-inspider-power-meter-debut/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Rotor 1×13 drivetrain</a> for MTB on a Revel</figcaption></figure><p>Since the derailleur is able to take up to a 52T rear cog, we leave it to the rider to determine the best gearing for their use: we offer 12s cassettes compatible with any 11s HG freehub body or 13s cassettes that work with our hubs and are capable of a wider range: 10-36, 10-39, 10-46 &amp; 10-52.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><figure id=\"attachment_259493\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-259493\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor.jpg\" alt=\"rotor 13 speed drivetrain 1x13 gravel bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"802\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-800x535.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-1068x714.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-628x420.jpg 628w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-800x535.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-1068x714.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21081418/Mosaic-drivetrain-rotor-628x420.jpg 628w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-259493\">Rotor’s 13 speed wide-range derailleur is compatible with their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/07/08/eb18-rotor-1x13-ratchets-up-drivetrain-wars-with-13-speed-hydraulic-1x-road-gravel-mtb-derailleur/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">road, MTB and TT groups</a>, and is suitable for gravel</figcaption></figure><p>This array of options, combined with the massive array of front ring sizes made possible by direct mount (26T-58T, round or oval), gives riders the largest array of gear choices on a group that provides the best versatility on the market.</p><p><strong>FSA: </strong>That is great question with a complicated answer. Gravel riding has been evolving and, in its relatively short existence as a category, is continuing to develop as new riders enter the market.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21080742/fsa-f-force-light-gravel-drivetrain-ultra-compact-crankset.jpg\"><img loading=