ikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21080742/fsa-f-force-light-gravel-drivetrain-ultra-compact-crankset.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21080742/fsa-f-force-light-gravel-drivetrain-ultra-compact-crankset-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21080742/fsa-f-force-light-gravel-drivetrain-ultra-compact-crankset-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21080742/fsa-f-force-light-gravel-drivetrain-ultra-compact-crankset-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21080742/fsa-f-force-light-gravel-drivetrain-ultra-compact-crankset-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21080742/fsa-f-force-light-gravel-drivetrain-ultra-compact-crankset-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21080742/fsa-f-force-light-gravel-drivetrain-ultra-compact-crankset-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/21080742/fsa-f-force-light-gravel-drivetrain-ultra-compact-crankset-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>We see MTB riders who have experiences with gear jumps have a different expectation from roadies, who may favor smaller jumps between gears. This may explain why riding history may favor 1x vs 2x systems. Then, when you include bike packers and new gravel riders, whose needs are quite different from that of a former road racer (in terms of power and speed, etc.) and we start to see a real mix of needs, wants, and requirements.</p><figure id=\"attachment_259492\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-259492\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-